#################################################################
#    Annotations
#################################################################

<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/EndEffector> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A robot component used to physically interact with objects, such as a gripper."@en ;
                                                       <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "end effector"@en ;
                                                       <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#relatedMatch> <http://www.ease-crc.org/ont/SOMA.owl#Gripper> ;
                                                       <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "This homework treats end effectors at a simplified level sufficient for graspability reasoning."@en .


<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/RobotAgent> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#closeMatch> <http://purl.org/ieee1872-owl/cora-bare#Robot> ;
                                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A robot or robot-controlled agent that can perceive, reason about, and manipulate objects in the task environment."@en ;
                                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "robot agent"@en ;
                                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#relatedMatch> <http://purl.org/ieee1872-owl/sumo-cora#Agent> ;
                                                      <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "The course term is aligned with CORA at the level of robot-as-agent or robot-as-system. It remains locally defined for the purposes of this homework."@en .


